content.description: Fun route with a bit of vertical and great cobbles.
When you see food, eat it.
content.location: Falls roughly between the two cottonwood trees

content.description: Slightly over vertical, a little pumpy.
content.location: Route on the far RH side of the wall.

content.description: **in a Homer Simpson voice*** "Mmmmmmm......french fries". Right of McAwesome on the slab. Climbs up to a shallow pod, then pulls a brief vertical section before the chains.
content.location: Second route right of the arete

content.description: Climb the Roadside Couloir. When you get to a ledge where that route is essentially over, step right onto the vertical wall and climb a few mover vertical bolts to chain anchors. The last 20' make the lower 50' worth it!
content.location: Start on roadside couloir, move right at the last bolt on that route.

content.description: This is the route that starts immediately outside the bottom right hand corner of the Roadside Couloir. It starts on the arete and climbs vertically to share anchors with Double The Beef For A Buck.
content.location: This is the route that starts immediately outside the bottom right hand corner of the Roadside Couloir.

content.description:
Start on the left corner (arete) of the Roadside Couloir and climb straight up. Avoids the roof and moves right to anchors above the

couloir. Surprisingly airy, fun geometry, exciting location.
content.location: Start on the left corner (arete) of the Roadside Couloir

content.description: This route follows the line of the ice climb by the same name. Anchors are on the left wall a little beyond the top of the couloir. We decided to use glue-ins because of seasonal water. Not hard, but harder than it looks.
content.location: Climbs the right hand side of the Couloir

content.description: I double-dog dare you to eat one.
content.location: Right of a slight depression in the wall. See photo for best beta

content.description: Good beginner route. If you want to climb High Dollar Value Meal, work left from the chains, scramble across the ledge to a set of belay anchors.
content.protection: Bolts, chain anchors under the roof.
content.location: Route starts on the left corner of the Roadside Couloir, trends left off of the arete and ends at the ledge under the roof.

content.description: Fun 2-pitch outing that gets you above the road. Climb Itty Bitty Biscuits or Double Beat Loaf. At the chains under the roof move left on the ledge, clipping a bolt where the roof pushes you off-balance. The belay station is located left of the start of pitch 2 about 15 feet to protect the belayer from potential rock fall. Crux is the second pitch.
Short with a little pump, a well protected and fun route. I think this is the third route Noah ever drilled and redpointed.

content.location: Leftmost route on the wall. Shares chains with High Dollar Value Meal and Itty Bitty Biscuits. The start is a bit of a bush-whack.

climbs.name: Double The Beef For A Buck

content.description: Climbs up the Couloir then cuts right, climbs around the arete then climbs the slightly less than vertical wall above to chains.
content.protection: Bolts, Chain anchors. Shares chains with McAwesome
content.location: Start in the couloir, then move right immediately below the pod.

content.description: Start on the left corner (arete) of the Roadside Couloir. Climb up into the light colored rock under the roof and go left where the the bolts split into two routes. Surmount the roof (crux, super fun moves!) and clip chains on the less-than-vertical wall above.
content.location: Start on the left corner (arete) of the Roadside Couloir.

content.description: The only better than bacon is MORE bacon.
content.location: This route is located where the wall starts to steepen.
